The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, March 30: The owner of an iron goods unit was arrested tonight for allegedly thrashing a female employee and cutting off her hair.

 Shib Shankar Ray suspected that Beauty Baidya, 30, regularly stole goods from his factory on West Canal Road, police said. Around 7 pm today, he allegedly beat her, cut off her hair and drove her out of the factory.

 Guwahati: Basu Patra, 25, a construction worker from Bengal, was killed and another wounded in a militant attack in the North Cachar Hills district of Assam on Wednesday.




